<div class=WordSection1 dir=RTL>



<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>To update the &quot;Firmware&quot; manually, first,
it is necessary for the device to be turned off.<span lang=AR-SA dir=RTL
style='font-size:13.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"B Nazanin"'></span></p></div>

<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>Then click on “Disconnect” in the “Preferences”
screen, so that the software will not send ping to device after the device is
turned on.<span lang=AR-SA dir=RTL style='font-size:13.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:"B Nazanin"'></span></p></div>

<div><p class=AAA-Aks dir=RTL><span dir=LTR>
 <img class="Image_Page"  src="~/Images/Tester/Updating_Firmware_of_Device_Manually_files/image001.png"
  o:title=""/>
</span><span lang=DE dir=LTR style='mso-ansi-language:DE'></span></p></div>

<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>To get started, the RS232 dongle needs to be
connected to its specific port on the back of the device Also, the device and
the laptop must be connected via LAN cable.<span lang=AR-SA dir=RTL
style='font-size:13.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"B Nazanin"'></span></p></div>

<div><p class=AAA-Aks dir=RTL><span dir=LTR>
 <img class="Image_Page"  src="~/Images/Tester/Updating_Firmware_of_Device_Manually_files/image002.jpg"
  o:title=""/>
<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> </span></span></p></div>

<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>It can be seen that, after the device turns on, the
&quot;ERROR&quot; light in the front panel of the device starts blinking.<span
lang=AR-SA dir=RTL style='font-size:13.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"B Nazanin"'></span></p></div>

<div><p class=AAA-Aks dir=RTL><span dir=LTR>
 <img class="Image_Page"  src="~/Images/Tester/Updating_Firmware_of_Device_Manually_files/image003.png"
  o:title=""/>
</span><span lang=DE dir=LTR style='mso-ansi-language:DE'></span></p></div>

<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>On the main page of the software, click on “Update
Firmware in Flash Mode<span dir=RTL></span><span dir=RTL></span><span
lang=AR-SA dir=RTL style='font-size:13.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:"B Nazanin"'><span dir=RTL></span><span dir=RTL></span>”.</span></p></div>

<div class = "card-panel hoverable"><p class=AAE-Normal dir=LTR>Then, you have to wait for the green bar to get
filled. After that, a message will be displayed. By clicking on “OK”, you can
finish updating the “Firmware”.<span lang=AR-SA dir=RTL style='font-size:13.0pt;
mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"B Nazanin"'></span></p></div>

<div><p class=AAA-Aks dir=RTL><span dir=LTR>
 <img class="Image_Page"  src="~/Images/Tester/Updating_Firmware_of_Device_Manually_files/image004.png"
  o:title=""/>
</span></p></div>

<p class=AAF-Normal dir=LTR>Turn off the device and unplug the RS232 dongle<span
dir=RTL></span><span dir=RTL></span><span lang=FA dir=RTL style='font-size:
10.0pt;mso-ansi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:"B Nazanin"'><span dir=RTL></span><span
dir=RTL></span>.</span></p></div>

